      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A middle aged known alcoholic was found lying semiconscious at his residence and was taken to ER. Laboratory studies showed a large anion gap, elevated blood alcohol levels - 245 mg/dL and low blood glucose - 38 mg/dL. The patient&rsquo;s large anion gap and hypoglycemia can be explained by which of the following?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2616872",
